On November 7, 2011, the President signed several laws, including H.R. 489, which clarifies the jurisdiction of the Secretary of the Interior with respect to the C.C. Cragin Dam and Reservoir in Arizona. H.R. 765, known as the "Ski Area Recreational Opportunity Enhancement Act of 2011," clarifies the authority of the Secretary of Agriculture regarding additional recreational uses of National Forest System land subject to ski area permits. H.R. 1843 designates a United States Postal Service facility as the John Pangelinan Gerber Post Office Building. H.R. 1975 designates another facility as the First Lieutenant Oliver Goodall Post Office Building. H.R. 2062 designates a facility as the Matthew A. Pucino Post Office. Lastly, H.R. 2149 designates a facility as the Cecil L. Heftel Post Office Building.